Shey cut his teeth working in a **marine biogeochemistry** lab while completing his Bachelor’s in Biology from the College of Creative Studies at the University of California, Santa Barbara.
There, he researched the chemical interactions between deep-sea microbes and their environment in the field and from the lab bench. <br>
After graduation, Shey worked for the climate technology start-up **Symbrosia**, where he helped commercialize cattle methane-reducing seaweed extracts by serving as the bridge between the R&D and business development departments. 
Eager to build upon his experience on the economic side of environmental impact ventures, Shey then worked with **Bhutan for Life**, a first of its kind partnership between the government of Bhutan, the World Wildlife Fund, and Green Climate fund. There he helped catalyze climate-smart initiatives in rural and indigenous communities throughout the country via strategic funding. 
<br>Now pursuing a Master’s degree at the **Bren School of Environmental Science and Management**, Shey is eager to build upon all these experiences to continue promoting environmental impact entrepreneurship and innovation. 
In his free time, Shey enjoys sleeping under the stars and film photography. 

